# Slicing Settings — Orca Slicer UI Paths

When the user asks about slicing settings, **give exact UI paths and values to fill in**. No "why" explanations unless asked.

## Format

**Process** (top bar) → **Tab** (Quality / Strength / Speed / etc.) → **Section** (collapsible) → **Field**: value

## Structural parts (engine mount, CF) — where to fill in what

| Tab | Section | Field | Value |
|-----|---------|-------|-------|
| Strength | Infill | Sparse Infill Density | `100%` |
| Strength | Infill | Sparse Infill Pattern | `grid` or `triangles` |
| Strength | Walls | Wall Loops | `5` |
| Strength | Top and Bottom Shells | Top Shell Layers | `5` |
| Strength | Top and Bottom Shells | Bottom Shell Layers | `5` |

## Orca Slicer UI structure (from screenshot)

- **Process** → **Global** → select process preset (e.g. `0.12mm Fine @Creality K1C`)
- **Quality** tab: Precision, Ironing, Wall generator, Walls and surfaces
- **Strength** tab: Infill, Walls, Top and Bottom Shells
- **Strength** tab: Infill, Top and Bottom Shells
- Use search (magnifying glass) to jump to a field by name

## Rule

Always specify: Tab → Section → Field → Value. Skip explanations unless the user asks.
